				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\chi }_{9}^{2}=38.46$$\end{document}χ92=38.46) with moderate change in α = 0.67 and minor improvement in R2-adjusted (0.67, out of sample two week ahead prediction). The retained covariates are listed in Table S3 and predictions with 95% confidence intervals are shown in Fig. 3.Figure 3
Observed (probable and confirmed) vs. two week ahead predicted transmission in all three core countries (top panel), in Guinea, Liberia, and Sierra Leone for both the expanding and the contracting phase of the epidemic, from left to right respectively. Red lines representing observed cases. 95% CI intervals are given for the predicted cases.
